**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

*   **Block Count & Layers:** There are 17 blocks across two structures. The left structure has 9 blocks and 4 layers, while the right structure has 8 blocks and 5 layers.
*   **Spatial Relationships:**
    *   **Left Structure:**
        *   The bottom layer consists of two blue blocks (index 5) standing vertically.
        *   A yellow rectangular block (index 10) sits horizontally on top of the blue blocks.
        *   A red block (index 3) and a green block (index 2) sit vertically next to each other on top of the yellow block.
        *   An orange triangular block (index 14) sits on top of the red and green blocks.
        *   The left structure has a house-like shape.
    *   **Right Structure:**
        *   Two orange cylindrical blocks (index 11) are positioned parallel to each other.
        *   A green rectangular block (index 6) is positioned horizontally on top of the cylinders.
        *   A red block (index 1) and a blue block (index 1) sit vertically on top of the green block.
        *   An orange triangular block (index 14) sits on top of the red and blue blocks.
        *   The right structure has a house-like shape.
